  "prompt": "How do I open a Demat account with SBI and do online trading?",
  "response": "To open a Demat account with SBI and start online trading, follow these steps:\n\n1. Online Account Opening Process:\n\u2022 Visit SBI Securities website (https://www.sbisec.com/)\n\u2022 Click on \"Open an Account\" or \"New Account\"\n\u2022 Fill online application form\n\u2022 Select account type (Regular/Basic)\n\n2. Required Documents:\n\u2022 PAN Card\n\u2022 Aadhar Card\n\u2022 Address Proof\n\u2022 Income Proof\n\u2022 Passport Size Photograph\n\u2022 Bank Account Details\n\u2022 Signature Proof\n\n3. Documentation Submission:\n\u2022 Upload scanned documents online\n\u2022 Alternatively, visit nearest SBI branch\n\u2022 Complete Know Your Customer (KYC) formalities\n\n4. Account Verification:\n\u2022 SBI will verify your documents\n\u2022 Background check process\n\u2022 Approval typically takes 3-5 working days\n\n5. Trading Account Activation:\n\u2022 Receive login credentials\n\u2022 Download SBI Securities mobile app\n\u2022 Complete online verification\n\u2022 Link bank account\n\u2022 Start trading\n\n6. Charges/Fees:\n\u2022 Account Opening: Typically free\n\u2022 Annual Maintenance Charges\n\u2022 Per Transaction Brokerage Fees\n\nRecommended: Consult SBI Securities directly for most updated procedure and specific requirements.",
